The paper deals with graph algorithms and optimization, specifically vertex sparsification and abstract rounding algorithms. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Among these, cs.DS and cs.CG are the most likely categories as they directly relate to graph algorithms and optimization. cs.IT and cs.LG are also possible categories as they deal with optimization and approximation algorithms. cs.NA is a less likely category, but it is still possible as the paper uses numerical techniques such as Earth-mover constraints.
